---
const title = "WASA Rawalpindi Water Bill Online — Check & Download March 2026";
const desc = "Check your WASA Rawalpindi water bill online by 8-digit C-Code. View your WASA RWP bill, download PDF, and get helpline details — free, no login required.";
const canonical = "https://pakistanbill.online/wasa-rawalpindi-bill/";
const faqs = [
  { q: "How do I check my WASA Rawalpindi water bill online in March 2026?", a: "Visit wasarwp.gop.pk and go to Customer Services → View Bill. Enter your 8-digit C-Code (Consumer Code) printed on any previous WASA Rawalpindi water bill and click Submit. Your complete bill for March 2026 appears with amount, due date, and consumption details." },
  { q: "What is the WASA Rawalpindi C-Code?", a: "The C-Code (Consumer Code) is an 8-digit number that uniquely identifies your WASA Rawalpindi water connection. It is printed at the top of every WASA Rawalpindi bill. Unlike WASA Lahore which calls it an Account Number, WASA Rawalpindi specifically labels it C-Code. Save it in your phone for monthly bill checking." },
  { q: "What is the WASA Rawalpindi helpline?", a: "WASA Rawalpindi customer service can be reached through the official portal wasarwp.gop.pk and by visiting WASA Rawalpindi's offices. For billing complaints and water supply issues, visit the WASA Rawalpindi head office in Rawalpindi or your nearest sub-office." },
  { q: "What areas does WASA Rawalpindi cover?", a: "WASA Rawalpindi covers Rawalpindi city and its surrounding urban areas including Saddar, Murree Road, Satellite Town, Chaklala, Adiala Road, and other Rawalpindi union councils. Islamabad's water supply is managed separately by CDA (Capital Development Authority). Rawalpindi Cantt areas may be under the Cantonment Board." },
  { q: "How do I pay my WASA Rawalpindi water bill online?", a: "Pay through bank mobile apps (HBL, MCB, Meezan) by selecting Water then WASA Rawalpindi and entering your 8-digit C-Code. You can also pay at 1-Link ATMs or at any WASA Rawalpindi payment counter. Visit wasarwp.gop.pk for the most current online payment options." },
  { q: "What charges are on a WASA Rawalpindi water bill?", a: "Your WASA Rawalpindi bill includes: water consumption charges based on metered usage, sewerage charges (a percentage of water charges), fixed service charges, and any arrears from previous months. Late payment surcharge applies after the grace period." },
  { q: "How do I download my WASA Rawalpindi duplicate bill?", a: "After your bill loads on wasarwp.gop.pk, click Print. In the browser print dialog, select Save as PDF to download your duplicate WASA Rawalpindi bill as a PDF file." },
  { q: "How do I file a billing complaint with WASA Rawalpindi?", a: "Visit wasarwp.gop.pk to find the current complaint mechanism, or visit your nearest WASA Rawalpindi sub-division office with your bill and CNIC. Note any complaint reference number provided." },
  { q: "How do I apply for a new WASA Rawalpindi water connection?", a: "Visit wasarwp.gop.pk → New Connection, or visit WASA Rawalpindi's head office. Required documents: CNIC, property ownership or tenancy documents, and site plan. Applicable connection fees depend on connection size and distance from the water main." },
  { q: "What is the difference between WASA Lahore and WASA Rawalpindi?", a: "WASA Lahore (Water and Sanitation Agency Lahore) and WASA Rawalpindi (WASA RWP) are separate government agencies serving separate cities. WASA Lahore covers Lahore. WASA Rawalpindi covers Rawalpindi. Both use 8-digit account identifiers but have different portals and helpline numbers. If you live in Islamabad, your water is supplied by CDA, not WASA." },
];
