        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:1rem;color:#134e4a;">About WASA Rawalpindi</h2>
        <p>Water and Sanitation Agency (WASA) Rawalpindi is the government authority responsible for water supply and sewerage in <strong>Rawalpindi city</strong> — Pakistan's fourth-largest city and a major commercial and military hub adjacent to the national capital Islamabad. WASA Rawalpindi operates under the Punjab government and provides treated piped water to residential, commercial, and industrial consumers throughout Rawalpindi's urban areas.</p>
        <p>Rawalpindi and Islamabad are twin cities sharing a geographic boundary. However, water supply for these cities is managed by separate authorities: <strong>WASA Rawalpindi</strong> covers Rawalpindi's civilian urban areas, while <strong>CDA (Capital Development Authority)</strong> supplies Islamabad's sectors. Rawalpindi Cantonment areas may be under the <strong>Rawalpindi Cantonment Board</strong>. If you receive a bill from WASA Rawalpindi (wasarwp.gop.pk), use the tool above with your 8-digit C-Code.</p>
        <p>WASA Rawalpindi uses a <strong>C-Code</strong> (Consumer Code) system — an 8-digit identifier for each connection. This is WASA Rawalpindi's specific terminology. When you pay through a bank app or 1-Link ATM, enter your 8-digit C-Code as the account number.</p>
      </section>

